parameters: \pop[2]I grab my bags from the trunk. An easy task, as I made sure to pack light.
\pop[2]The point of this journey was to leave my baggage behind. Not carry it with me.
\pop[2]Isaac steps in to help out, and I turn to face the house. My new home.
\pop[3]The pictures don't do it justice, do they?
It has its quirks, but it's served all of us just fine.
\i[5]"It's beautiful. I'm glad to finally be here."
\i[6]"It was better in the pictures, to be honest."
\i[0]"I wish I had a place like this back at home."
\i[5]"It's beautiful. I'm glad to finally be here."
\pop[3]And we're glad to have you, Delta.

\pop[3]No problem. You're more than welcome in my home.
\pop[3]I hope you'll get along well with Dante, though. He's a bit of a handful.
At least I'll know it wasn't my fault if you ever jump ship.
\pop[2]He smiles at me before closing the trunk and locking everything up.
\pop[2]I carry two of my bags, while he carries the other two. An equal team.
\pop[2]We make our way to the front door, and place everything down in sync.
\pop[2]He pulls out his phone and holds it up against the entry scanner.
\pop[2]A small beep sounds, and then a moment later, the door unlocks.
\pop[2]At least the security system protecting this house was solid.
\pop[5]\c[23]You may leave the house \c[10](2)\c[23] more times today.
\pop[5]\c[23]Remember, a good score makes a good citizen.
\pop[3]I definitely muted this stuff the other day.
Dante must've freaked out and removed my mods. \c[14]Again\c[0].
\pop[2]That's true. Tampering with \c[23]The System\c[0] at home was a big deal.
\pop[2]I don't think Isaac was up to anything shady, though. He probably just likes silence.
\pop[2]Typically, people would mess with \c[23]The System\c[0] when they had something worth hiding.
\pop[3]With how tired you were in the car, I guess you deserve a nap.
But don't mess up your sleep schedule. We gotta watch that report tomorrow.
\pop[2]I nod, and now that the door is open, we pick everything up.
\pop[2]Using his shoulder to nudge the door open, we slowly enter the house.
\pop[2]I've seen so many pictures of this place, but seeing it for real was incredible.
\pop[2]The living room is incredibly spacious. It looked much smaller when I saw it online.
\pop[2]One thing that stands out to me however, is the lack of integrated technology.
\pop[2]It looks like a living room frozen in time around thirty years ago. Interesting.
\pop[2]This sight, combined with how Isaac acted at the door, revealed one thing.
\pop[2]He must not be a big fan of \c[23]The System\c[0]. Not everyone is, though. It's fine.
\pop[2]I think it's actually cool how quickly you learn stuff about people after meeting them for real.
\pop[2]I can see Dante sitting on the couch, engulfed in his phone.
\pop[2]Isaac seems a little mad, and confronts him immediately.
\pop[3]Hey Dante, did you mess with those changes I made the other day?
I thought I told you to play along with those. I do it for a reason.
\pop[2]Dante's ears perk up, and he immediately rises from the couch.
\pop[2]I can tell he let his guard down, but he was eagerly awaiting our entrance.
\pop[2]Whatever kind of first impression he was planning, his lack of awareness destroyed it.
\pop[4]Man, can't you see that I'm looking out for you?
\pop[4]If they found out about your tinkering, they'd dock you points. Or worse.
I'm sure Delta has my back here. Messing with \c[23]Argus\c[0] just isn't worth it.
\pop[2]Putting me on the spot the second after you meet me? Nice.
\pop[6]I scratch my head, and Isaac looks at me, likely expecting my support.
\i[3]"I have Isaac's back here. His house, his rules."
\i[3]"I agree with Dante. Ideals aside, legal trouble is never worth it."
\i[3]"I have Isaac's back here. His house, his rules."
\pop[4]True, but it's only a matter of time before we're tried as "accomplices".
\pop[4]\c[23]Argus\c[0] may be many things, but forgiving isn't one of them.
Look at how the \c[10]zeros\c[0] are treated. See what I mean?
\i[3]"I agree with Dante. Ideals aside, legal trouble is never worth it."
\pop[4]Knew I could count on you. Especially after everything Isaac said.
\pop[4]He may call me stubborn, but he respects you way more.
I think you might be the one to finally knock some sense into him.
\pop[3]I know I brought it up, but I don't want our first meeting to be an argument.
Besides, I work for \c[23]Argus\c[0]. I know what I'm doing when I make "changes".
\pop[4]If by "work", you mean "enforce \c[23]The System\c[0] on others", then sure.
You do a lot of things that you'd report other people for doing.
\pop[3]Hey, not fair! I may tamper with some hardware, but I never break laws.
\pop[3]You'd be surprised how much you can bend the rules without breaking them.
I don't know how many times I have to say this, but please, just trust me.
\pop[4]Fine. Still the best deal on housing I've come across.
\pop[4]Can you at least tamper with \c[23]The System\c[0] and let us skip that report tomorrow?
If you're going to bend the rules, might as well do something practical with it.
\pop[3]That one toes the line way too much. I'll have to pass.
It's only an hour. Just put in some earbuds or something.
\pop[3]I'm gonna go help Delta unpack and get a bit of rest in.
\pop[4]Alright, fair enough. But if \c[23]Argus\c[0] ever comes knocking?
Just know that I won't hesitate before turning you in.
\pop[3]That eager to get me in handcuffs, huh?
\pop[2]Dante steps forward with a laugh, and holds out his hand.
\pop[4]I was hoping to hang out for a bit, but I get that you're tired.
If you want to bond or whatever, you know where to find me.
\pop[2]I shake his hand, and give him a soft nod.
\pop[2]If we're gonna be roommates, it makes sense to bond.
\pop[2]I let him know that I'll find him as soon as I get some shuteye.
\pop[4]Perfect. And make sure to prod Isaac for me.
He's way too tight-lipped about the nightclub outing this weekend.
\pop[4]Your fault; keeping secrets from your friends like that.
\pop[2]I shrug. I knew that Isaac would plan a party, so it's no big deal.
\pop[2]Dante smirks at me, and then returns to his spot on the couch.
\pop[2]I've met people like him before. An agent of social chaos.
Maybe I should start trusting you a bit more often.
Add Taylor to the mix, and we'll do great things.
\pop[2]Isaac scoffs, but then quickly displays a large smile as Dante becomes lost in his phone.
\pop[3]Head always in the clouds, that one.
Almost prefer when he locks himself in his room to write.
\pop[3]Before we pick up your luggage though, hold on a sec.
This has been a long time coming, and I never got a chance to at the airport.
\pop[2]He steps forward, and wraps his arms around me.
\pop[2]I do the same, and we stand there for a few moments, in a tight embrace.
\pop[2]I have no idea why this is the first time I felt it, but this really was the fresh start I wanted.
And just like Dante said -- great things.
\pop[2]I release the hug, with a big smile on my face.
\pop[2]This was it. Finally. The start of my new life.
